caption.p: Histology analysis in immunized A129 mice after ZIKV infection.

tr.th: Patchy, Meningeal Infiltration by Inflammatory Cells
Poorly Defined Areas of White Pulp with Large Mononuclear Cells
Mature PMNs in Red Pulp Sinuses

fn.p: Histological lesions were assessed in ChAdOx1-EDIII vaccinated mice and control groups. As a comparison, mice were vaccinated with a reference vaccine consisting of a ChAdOx1 prME Î”TM, which provided 100% protection against the ZIKV challenge. The table shows the day of culling for each mice. For the brain and spleen, 5 and 3 different microscopic measurement observations were performed, respectively. Scores are within normal limits (WNL) (dark green), minimal (light green), mild (yellow), moderate (dark red), and severe (light red).
